                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="488146" author="paf0186" created="Wed, 18 Feb 2026 20:13:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing as duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19750&quot; title=&quot;interop: master+b2_15 client can&amp;#39;t access changelog due to missing mdt_body in open request&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19750&quot;&gt;LU-19750&lt;/a&gt;. The changelog failures on the master CI pipeline are all interop (master client + b2_16 server) and are caused by the mdt_changelog_allow() / mdt_body issue tracked there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="488136" author="paf0186" created="Wed, 18 Feb 2026 19:22:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Investigation findings:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Alllustremasterpipelinefailuresareinterop&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;All lustre-master pipeline failures are interop&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Every failing session on lustre-master is interop: master el10 client + b2_16 server (SLES 15 SP6 or Ubuntu 24.04). There are no master-on-master failures for this bug on the lustre-master pipeline. The lustre-reviews failures are from broken &quot;custom&quot; test sessions (116 failures across the board) and are likely environmental.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Twodistinctfailuremodes&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Two distinct failure modes&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;1. changelog_mask=+hsm set_param fails (ENOENT, rc=2)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Tests: sanity-sec test_35, sanity test_64e&lt;br/&gt;
Error: &lt;tt&gt;lustre-MDT0000: changelog_mask=+hsm failed: 2&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
This is a &lt;tt&gt;do_facet&lt;/tt&gt; operation (runs locally on the b2_16 MDS via SSH). &lt;tt&gt;lctl set_param mdd.lustre-MDT0000.changelog_mask=+hsm&lt;/tt&gt; returns ENOENT. This suggests the mdd changelog parameter path doesn&apos;t exist on the b2_16 server &#8212; possibly a b2_16-specific initialization issue on SLES 15 SP6/Ubuntu 24.04.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;2. Changelog llog access fails&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Tests: sanity test_60i (&quot;can&apos;t read changelog&quot;), sanity-hsm test_220A/220a/221/222a-d (&quot;expected changelog was not emitted&quot;), lustre-rsync-test test_1A/1a/2a/2c/3a&lt;br/&gt;
This is the llog client&#8594;server RPC access issue covered by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19750&quot; title=&quot;interop: master+b2_15 client can&amp;#39;t access changelog due to missing mdt_body in open request&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19750&quot;&gt;LU-19750&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Rootcause%3ALU19750&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Root cause: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19750&quot; title=&quot;interop: master+b2_15 client can&amp;#39;t access changelog due to missing mdt_body in open request&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19750&quot;&gt;LU-19750&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The core issue is &lt;tt&gt;mdt_changelog_allow()&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;lustre/mdt/mdt_internal.h&lt;/tt&gt;. On current master (2.17.50), since &lt;tt&gt;LUSTRE_VERSION_CODE &amp;gt;= OBD_OCD_VERSION(2, 17, 3, 0)&lt;/tt&gt;, the function returns &lt;tt&gt;false&lt;/tt&gt; when &lt;tt&gt;mti_body&lt;/tt&gt; is NULL &#8212; denying changelog access.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Timeline:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Jan 7: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63231&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;815dfd3451&lt;/a&gt; merged (client fix: send mdt_body in llog open for nameless llogs)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Feb 5: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63272&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;1c0d9f16e4&lt;/a&gt; merged (server fix: relax version check)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Feb 5: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63823&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;183eb9af3f&lt;/a&gt; merged (REVERT of server fix &#8212; caused 100% LBUG crash in sanity-sec test_35)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Current state: the client-side fix is applied (master clients send mdt_body), but the server-side fix is reverted. This means:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Master client &#8594; master server: works (client sends mdt_body, server accepts it)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Master client &#8594; b2_16 server: the new request format from the client may not be handled correctly by older servers&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;b2_16 client &#8594; master server: client doesn&apos;t send mdt_body, master server denies access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This ticket may be a sub-issue of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19750&quot; title=&quot;interop: master+b2_15 client can&amp;#39;t access changelog due to missing mdt_body in open request&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19750&quot;&gt;LU-19750&lt;/a&gt;. The changelog_mask set_param ENOENT on b2_16 servers needs separate investigation with access to a b2_16 test environment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
